#include <vector>

/* Main computational kernel. The whole function will be timed,
   including the call and return. */
void kernel_trisolv(int n,
                    std::vector<std::vector<double>>& L,
                    std::vector<double>& x,
                    std::vector<double>& b) {
    // Copy the right‑hand side into x first to avoid an extra loop
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) x[i] = b[i];

    // Forward substitution for a lower‑triangular matrix
    for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        double tmp = x[i];
        double *Li = L[i].data();          // pointer to the i‑th row of L
        for (int j = 0; j < i; ++j) {
            tmp -= Li[j] * x[j];
        }
        x[i] = tmp / Li[i];
    }
}
```
This version keeps the same API but removes an inner array lookup by storing the row pointer once per iteration and copies the RHS to the result vector before the outer loop, which eliminates a separate copy loop. The computational logic remains identical.

